commText: Head and Abhishek Sharma are at the crease. Head is on strike. Arshdeep Singh will open the attack
Arshdeep Singh to Head, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Arshdeep Singh to Head, out Bowled!! Wow! What a start! One impact sub gets the other. SRH dealt an early blow as Head walks back first ball. Good length delivery and didn't move much, Head stayed rooted to the crease and is tad late in getting his bat down, the ball skids through and sneaks under to hit the off-stump. Head b Arshdeep Singh 0(1)
Rahul Tripathi, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Arshdeep Singh to Tripathi, FOUR, shot! Just an extended forward block and the ball races away. On a length and angled across, Tripathi gets a good stride forward and opens the bat face, the ball pings off the middle and races through cover-point
Arshdeep Singh to Tripathi, no run, I0$ back of a length around the hips, Tripathi turns it in front of mid-wicket
Arshdeep Singh to Tripathi, FOUR, easy pickings. Poor from Arshdeep. No third man and he goes short of length outside off, Tripathi uses the pace and just elevates it over short third
Arshdeep Singh to Tripathi, no run, I0$ back of a length on off, Tripathi defends it to the off-side
Arshdeep Singh to Tripathi, leg byes, 1 run, stifled appeal for LBW. Swinging into the pads, Tripathi misses the flick and the ball deflects to square leg
SRH batters out on first ball of an IPL innings \nShikhar Dhawan vs CSK, Mumbai WS, 2018 Qualifier 1 \nTravis Head vs PBKS, Hyderabad, 2024
Rishi Dhawan, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Rishi Dhawan to Tripathi, 1 run, short and outside off, Tripathi cuts straight to deep backward point
Rishi Dhawan to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, leg-lined delivery, Abhishek nudges it into the vacant mid-wicket pocket
Wide slip in place
Rishi Dhawan to Tripathi, no run, charges down and Dhawan keeps it outside off, Tripathi has a swing and miss

Rishi Dhawan to Tripathi, SIX, lovely shot! Just a free flow of the bat and the ball sails over the rope. Fullish delivery and Tripathi lofts through the line, clean strike and no trouble clearing the fence
Some issue with the ball. Nitin Menon has called for a replacement. Seems like a bit of threading or the leather has come off after the big hit.

Rishi Dhawan to Tripathi, FOUR, shot! Dhawan goes full and at the stumps, Tripathi leans forward and drives it with a straight bat to the right of mid-on. This was all timing as the ball races away to the fence
Rishi Dhawan to Tripathi, FOUR, I0$ delivery with ample width, Tripathi opens the bat face and steers it behind square on the off-side
Arshdeep Singh to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, streaky! Arshdeep goes short at Abhishek, the latter takes it on and goes for the pull, the top-edge flies fine and beats the fielder in the deep
Arshdeep Singh to Abhishek Sharma, no run, I0$ on a length and swinging away, Abhishek has a slash and is beaten on the outside edge
Arshdeep Singh to Abhishek Sharma, no run, I0$ back of a length and bit of extra bounce, Abhishek swings through the line and is beaten again. Arshdeep has a stare at his state-mate

Arshdeep Singh to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, this time Abhishek connects. Short of length delivery and Abhishek is in a good position to play the pull, hits it in front of square and to the vacant deep mid-wicket region
Arshdeep Singh to Abhishek Sharma, no run, charges down and is met by a short of length delivery, has a go with a cross-batted shot but the extra bounce beats him. Jitesh collects it over his head

Arshdeep Singh to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, boundary or nothing in this over. Arshdeep does not get the height on the short of length delivery, sits up nicely for Abhishek to play the pull and he smashes it over long leg
Rishi Dhawan to Tripathi, no run, short and outside off, Tripathi cuts it straight to backward point

Rishi Dhawan to Tripathi, leg byes, FOUR, strays down leg, Tripathi misses the glance and the ball beats a diving Jitesh. It seemed to have brushed the pad on the way but umpire signals wides. Punjab take the review and get the decision overturned
Rishi Dhawan to Tripathi, no run, short and outside off, Tripathi toe-ends the cut straight to short third

Rishi Dhawan to Tripathi, 1 run, in the air and over short fine. Angled in and Tripathi tries to help it along the way, but gets a thick top-edge and the ball flies over the infield, lands safely and the fielder gets there to keep it down to a single
Dhawan goes round the wicket
Rishi Dhawan to Abhishek Sharma, no run, charges down and is yorked by a slower ball, Abhishek has a swing and a miss

Rishi Dhawan to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, that ruins the over. Slanted in from back of a length and at Dhawan's pace, it is easy pickings for Abhishek, he swivels and sends it sailing into the second tier at fine leg
Harshal Patel, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harshal Patel to Tripathi, 1 run, good length ball around off, Tripathi pats it to the off-side and quickly crosses over
Round the wicket to Abhishek

Harshal Patel to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, streaky but the ball has gone the distance. Unlucky for Harshal. Slower ball around off, Abhishek swings across the line and gets a top-edge, the ball flies over short third and just crosses the rope

Harshal Patel to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, this is better. He shimmies down and gives himself room, lofts it over the off-side field and the ball lands just inside the rope. Not off the middle but effective
Sweeper out now
Harshal Patel to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, off-pace delivery outside off, Abhishek slices it on the bounce to sweeper cover

Harshal Patel to Tripathi, no ball, SIX, that's a horrible delivery. High full toss well over the waist, Tripathi was ducking but went through with the shot, gets a good connection and the ball travels the distance at long leg. Free-hit coming up
Harshal Patel to Tripathi, wide, tries to keep it away from the batter's range and sprays it outside off, Tripathi leaves and the free-hit stays
Harshal Patel to Tripathi, 2 runs, full pitcher around off, Tripathi slices it over the off-side field and just manages to clear the backtracking fielder
Harshal Patel to Tripathi, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshal Patel to Tripathi, out Caught by Arshdeep Singh!! Harshal goes for 22 but manages to break the partnership. This was the slower ball that dips on the batter, Tripathi does not pick it and is through the loft early, miscues it straight up and Arshdeep settles under it near mid-off and takes it calmly. Tripathi c Arshdeep Singh b Harshal Patel 33(18) [4s-4 6s-2]

Over Summary (1-5) -> Arshdeep strikes in the first over, Head is gone for a duck -> Rishi Dhawan concedes 16 runs in his first over -> Abhishek and Tripathi on the charge, dealing in boundaries -> 50 up for Sunrisers Hyderabad in 4 overs -> Harshal bowls an expensive over but gets Tripathi's wicket
Nitish Reddy, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Rishi Dhawan to Abhishek Sharma, wide, full and outside off, Abhishek gives the charge and does not bother to go chasing, wide called
Rishi Dhawan to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, slower ball outside off, Abhishek slices it over the point region and there's a sweeper in the deep
Did you know? SRH have become the second team to hit 150 sixes in a T20 series, after RCB, who have hit 157 this year so far.
Rishi Dhawan to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, tight single. Fullish delivery and Nitish drives it straight to mid-off, he calls for the single and makes it in even though he has to run around the bowler
Rishi Dhawan to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, full and outside off, Abhishek drives it to long-off
Rishi Dhawan to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, short and outside off, Nitish cracks it straight to sweeper cover
Rishi Dhawan to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, slower ball outside off, Abhishek fetches the flat-batted shot but makes a very good connection as the ball travels 82 meters in the long-on direction
Rishi Dhawan to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, low full toss outside off, Abhishek toe-ends the drive to extra cover

Timeout! SRH lost Head first ball but that has not held them back. Tripathi came in and started playing his shots before Abhishek got into the act. The pair added a 50+ stand in quick time and they have once again bossed the powerplay. Punjab need wickets and a couple of them to pull things back
Rahul Chahar, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, advances down the wicket and slogs across the line, gets a single at long-on
Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, no run, sharp leg-break on off, Nitish Reddy opens the bat face, steering it to backward point
Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, no run, tad fuller on middle, grips and turns, Nitish Reddy nudges it back to Rahul Chahar
Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, tad short on middle and leg, worked through the on-side for a single

Rahul Chahar to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, on the shorter side, Abhishek Sharma pulls it to deep mid-wicket. Was in the air for a long time, but he didn't time it well enough. Hence the fielder couldn't get there in time
Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, plays this towards the leg-side for a single to end the over
Harshal Patel [1.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack
Harshal Patel to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, short of a length on middle and leg, nudged to long-on for a single
Harshal Patel to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, superb fielding. Was driven crisply by Abhishek Sharma and Prabhsimran dives to his left to grab it. Does well to get rid of the ball quickly too
Harshal Patel to Nitish Reddy, no run, on the shorter side outside off, Nitish Reddy shoulders arms
Harshal Patel to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, drifting on the pads, Nitish Reddy works it through mid-wicket for a single

Harshal Patel to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, first boundary after the powerplay. Width on offer and Abhishek Sharma carves it through backward point, manages to beat the fielder who puts in a dive near the boundary

Harshal Patel to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, brings up his fifty in style. Tad fuller, tad slower and Abhishek Sharma stays put to loft it right over the bowler's head. Impeccable timing as the ball races away to the fence. 11 runs from the over
Highest powerplay scores for SRH 125/0 vs DC, Delhi, 2024 107/0 vs LSG, Hyderabad, 2024 84/2 vs PBKS, Hyderabad, 2024 81/1 vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024 79/0 vs KKR, Hyderabad, 2017
Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, 2 runs, quicker through the air on a fuller length, Nitish Reddy drives it to deep extra cover where Harshal stops it just before the boundary by flicking it away
Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, full and straight on off, Nitish Reddy pushes it to the off-side for a single
Rahul Chahar to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, googly outside off, Abhishek slices it through cover for a single

Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, SIX, Nitish Reddy joins the party. Swings this towards deep mid-wicket where Shashank takes a catch, however, he steps over the boundary in the process. Takes it on the second attempt but couldn't keep the ball inside
Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, played through cover by Nitish Reddy for a single
Rahul Chahar to Abhishek Sharma, no run, fraction short outside off, Abhishek Sharma cuts it to point
Most sixes by an Indian batter in an IPL season 39 - Abhishek Sharma (SRH, 2024) 38 - Virat Kohli (RCB, 2016) 37 - Rishabh Pant (DC, 2018) 37 - Virat Kohli (RCB, 2024) 35 - Shivam Dube (CSK, 2023)
Harpreet Brar, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Harpreet Brar to Nitish Reddy, no run, quicker through the air on leg, hits the batter on the pads
Harpreet Brar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, shimmies down the wicket and squeezes this to long-on for one

Harpreet Brar to Abhishek Sharma, 5 wides, Abhishek Sharma was down the wicket to have a go at Harpreet Brar and the bowler fires it down the leg-side. Does well to beat the batter but Jitesh couldn't gather the ball, five wides called
Harpreet Brar to Abhishek Sharma, no run, slightly slow, Abhishek Sharma swings across, gets hit on the pads though

Harpreet Brar to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, just clears the boundary. A full toss by Harpreet Brar and Abhishek Sharma launches it over the bowler's head. Clears the fielder in the deep and the 50-run stand comes up
Harpreet Brar to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, back-to-back sixes. Down the wicket to heave the floated delivery over wide long-on for half-a-dozen more
Harpreet Brar to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, full toss by Harpreet Brar and Abhishek Sharma has heaved it to long-on for one

Over Summary (6-10) -> SRH record their third highest powerplay score in IPL - 84/2 -> Chahar bowls a quiet over, just 4 runs -> Abhishek brings up his fifty off 21 balls -> Shashank can't hold onto a catch off Nitish -> Brar concedes 19 runs in his first over
Shashank Singh, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Shashank Singh to Abhishek Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Shashank Singh to Abhishek Sharma, out Caught by Shivam Singh!! Shashank Singh failed with the bat today, but he comes into the attack and strikes on his first ball. Gets the set batter as I can see a drizzle in the background. A full and wide delivery outside off and Abhishek Sharma slices it towards Shivam at deep cover point. Taken comfortably and that brings an end to Abhishek's pyrotechnics. Abhishek Sharma c Shivam Singh b Shashank Singh 66(28) [4s-5 6s-6]
Heinrich Klaasen, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Shashank Singh to Klaasen, 1 run, short of a length on middle and leg, Klaasen nudges it to long-on for a single
Shashank Singh to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, short of a length around off, nips back in as Nitish Reddy gets an inside edge on to the pads
Shashank Singh to Klaasen, 1 run, banged in short on middle and leg, Klaasen swivel-pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single
Shashank Singh to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, slower delivery on off, Nitish Reddy whips it through mid-wicket for a single
Shashank Singh to Klaasen, 1 run, pitched up by the bowler on off, Klaasen drives it to long-off for a single
Rahul Chahar [2.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Klaasen, 1 run, tossed up delivery on off, Klaasen drives it to mid-off for a single

Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, SIX, the sixes keep coming! No stopping SRH batters. This was a half-tracker, Nitish Reddy rocks back in the crease and hammers the pull over deep mid-wicket. Clean as a whistle!
Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, no run, width on offer as Nitish Reddy cuts it to point
Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, FOUR, more runs! Goes down on his knee to play the reverse sweep, gets a top edge that flies over the keeper's head. Can't place a fielder there and that's four more
Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, wide, short and wide outside off, misses the tramline by a long way
Rahul Chahar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, driven along the turf to long-off for a single

Rahul Chahar to Klaasen, SIX, 150 up for SRH! Tad full, not that short. That's the class of Klaasen though, gets into position quickly and picks it over deep mid-wicket, goes the distance. Sunrisers in a hurry to get things done
Harpreet Brar [1.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Harpreet Brar to Nitish Reddy, leg byes, 1 run, down the wicket as the bowler goes full and quick, off the pads towards the off-side
Harpreet Brar to Klaasen, no run, quicker delivery on off, punched back to the bowler by Klaasen
Harpreet Brar to Klaasen, no run, tad slow as the ball grips into the surface, Klaasen blocks it back to Harpreet Brar
Harpreet Brar to Klaasen, SIX, huge! Harpreet Brar goes flat and Klaasen rocks back to launch it over long-on with minimum effort. Result? Maximum!
Harpreet Brar to Klaasen, 1 run, pushed through on a length, Klaasen knocks it to long-off with soft hands

Harpreet Brar to Nitish Reddy, SIX, both the batters dealing in sixes. On a length around middle and leg, Nitish Reddy gets into position quickly and towers it over long-on, clears the fielder in the deep as SRH require 48 more in 42 balls
Harshal Patel [2.0-0-33-1] is back into the attack

Harshal Patel to Klaasen, 2 runs, short of a length on middle and leg, Klaasen works it through the leg-side with soft hands, challenges the fielder's arm and takes two. Excellent running between the wickets. The throw came in at the bowler's end, however, Reddy was in with a dive
Harshal Patel to Klaasen, FOUR, short of a length around off, Klaasen punches it through cover and manages to beat the fielder inside the ring. No one in the deep and that's four more
Harshal Patel to Klaasen, 1 run, on a length around off, knocked to long-off for a single
Harshal Patel to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, squeezed through backward point for a single
Harshal Patel to Klaasen, 1 run, played towards the off-side for a single by Klaasen
Harshal Patel to Nitish Reddy, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshal Patel to Nitish Reddy, out Caught by Shivam Singh!! End of a handy innings by Nitish Reddy. This was short and wide outside off, Nitish Reddy throws his hands at it and slices it straight to the fielder at deep backward point. Taken with ease by Shivam Singh. SRH need only 39 runs more.. Nitish Reddy c Shivam Singh b Harshal Patel 37(25) [4s-1 6s-3]
Shahbaz Ahmed, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Arshdeep Singh [2.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack
Arshdeep Singh to Klaasen, 1 run, on a length around off, Klaasen slices it through point for one
Arshdeep Singh to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, fraction short on middle and leg, Shahbaz Ahmed looks to work it away, gets hit on the thigh pad due to the bounce

Arshdeep Singh to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, dropped at deep square leg! Shahbaz Ahmed had pulled this short ball away and Harshal in the deep puts down a regulation catch. Arshdeep not pleased with that effort
Arshdeep Singh to Klaasen, 2 runs, short in length on off, Klaasen goes for a pull, gets it off the cue end past the keeper, a couple of runs taken
Arshdeep Singh to Klaasen, 1 run, on the shorter side, quicker delivery as the batsman gets hurried up. Goes for the pull and mistimes it towards the leg-side, a single taken
Arshdeep Singh to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, fine over by Arshdeep Singh. A low full toss on middle and leg, Shahbaz Ahmed flicks it to wide long-on for a single

Over Summary (11-15) -> Shashank gets the big wicket of Abhishek -> Chahar is smashed for 19 runs in his third over -> Brar is hammered for two sixes -> Harshal has a second as Nitish holes out for 37 -> Shahbaz is dropped on 0, Arshdeep the unlucky bowler
Timeout! Sunrisers Hyderabad in control as they need only 33 runs more in 5 overs to get over the line. Plenty of batting remaining so this should be a stroll in the park..
Harshal Patel to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, short and wide outside off, Shahbaz Ahmed carves it over cover-point for a single
Harshal Patel to Klaasen, no run, on the shorter side, Klaasen goes for a pull, gets beaten on the top edge
Harshal Patel to Klaasen, no run, back of a length around off, Klaasen guides it back to Harshal Patel
Harshal Patel to Klaasen, wide, Harshal Patel goes short again and the umpire has called an overhead wide this time

Harshal Patel to Klaasen, FOUR, on a length outside off, Klaasen drives it to wide long-off where the fielder stops it with a slide. It was Shashank Singh who flicked the ball away but he was in contact with the boundary
Harshal Patel to Klaasen, 1 run, pitched up by the bowler on middle, Klaasen drives it to long-on for a single
Harshal Patel to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, full length delivery on off, Shahbaz Ahmed drives it to mid-off
Equation: 26 runs required in 4 overs..
Arshdeep Singh to Klaasen, 2 runs, pitched up by the bowler on off, Klaasen drives it past the fielder at cover and takes a couple of runs

Arshdeep Singh to Klaasen, FOUR, terrible fielding. Short of a length around off and Klaasen punches it towards cover where the fielder (Shivam Singh) makes a school boy error, is casual in getting down to stop it, gifting away a boundary. Jitesh Sharma immediately moves him away to a different field position
Arshdeep Singh to Klaasen, no run, back of a length around off, knocked into the off-side by Klaasen
Arshdeep Singh to Klaasen, wide, way too short as the ball sails over the batter's head
Arshdeep Singh to Klaasen, 1 run, back of a length on middle and leg, clipped to mid-on for a single by Klaasen
Arshdeep Singh to Shahbaz Ahmed, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Arshdeep Singh to Shahbaz Ahmed, out Caught by Shashank Singh!! Pitched up by the bowler on off, Shahbaz Ahmed drives this powerfully but Shashank Singh at cover takes a sharp low catch. Shahbaz Ahmed c Shashank Singh b Arshdeep Singh 3(6)
Abdul Samad, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Arshdeep Singh to Abdul Samad, 1 run, back of a length around middle and leg, Abdul Samad works it to long-on for a single
Equation: 17 runs required in 18 balls now..
Rahul Chahar [3.0-0-34-0] is back into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Abdul Samad, no run, sharp leg break on off, Abdul Samad taps it into the off-side
Rahul Chahar to Abdul Samad, 1 run, on the pads, worked through the leg-side for a single
Rahul Chahar to Klaasen, 1 run, 200 up for SRH. Quicker through the air, tad fuller, Klaasen gets an inside edge towards the leg-side
Rahul Chahar to Abdul Samad, no run, tad short on off, Abdul Samad cuts it off the back foot to backward point

Rahul Chahar to Abdul Samad, SIX, the chase would have been done by now had Abdul Samad walked out to bat before Shahbaz. Dances out of the crease and launches it over long-off as SRH inch close to victory
Rahul Chahar to Abdul Samad, 1 run, quicker through the air on middle, Abdul Samad knocks it to long-on for a single
Harpreet Brar [2.0-0-32-0] is back into the attack
Harpreet Brar to Abdul Samad, 1 run, full and straight on off, Abdul Samad gets an inside edge through the leg-side, takes a single
Harpreet Brar to Klaasen, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Harpreet Brar to Klaasen, out Bowled!! Okay then, we have some more drama. Someone who can clear the boundary at will, tries something funny. Clearly not his strength. Looks to play the scoop and ends up exposing the stumps. Gets cleaned up and the crowd in Hyderabad will have to wait for some more time for the inevitable. Klaasen b Harpreet Brar 42(26) [4s-3 6s-2]
Sanvir Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harpreet Brar to Sanvir Singh, 1 run, nudged to long-on by Sanvir Singh for a single
Harpreet Brar to Abdul Samad, 1 run, punched to long-on by Abdul Samad for a single
Harpreet Brar to Sanvir Singh, no run, tad short on off, punched to cover by Sanvir Singh
Harpreet Brar to Sanvir Singh, 1 run, shimmies down the wicket to drive it to long-off for a single
Equation: 4 runs required in 6 balls now..
Atharva Taide, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Atharva Taide to Sanvir Singh, FOUR, Game. Set. Match! Finally. Sanvir Singh smashes this right over the bowler's head and SRH win by 4 wickets. Handshakes all around as Sunrisers register another win and solidify their chances of finishing in top two. Everything depends on the result of next game now..

19:17 Local Time, 13:47 GMT, 19:17 IST: Sunrisers Hyderabad jump to the second spot in the points table as a result of this clinical win. Punjab Kings played brilliantly earlier in the day as their top three batters - all of them clicked. Taide and Rossouw played lovely knocks, while Prabhsimran scored 70-odd as the Kings finished with a daunting total of 214/5. With the kind of form Sunrisers Hyderabad batters have been in, the target wasn't going to challenge them. They did lose Travis Head in the first over of the run chase, however, Abhishek and Tripathi counterattacked in the powerplay and shifted the pressure back on the Punjab bowlers. Nitish Reddy and Klaasen chipped in with pivotal knocks and although they lost a few wickets towards the end, they got over the line in the final over. The result of the next game decides whether it's Sunrisers or Rajasthan to join KKR for Qualifier 1. Stay around for the presentations..

Jitesh Sharma | PBKS captain: It was fun out there. The boys fought really hard and we enjoyed a lot. Nice game without the overseas players. The discussion won't help till you imply on the ground. We have to play according to the wicket and plan accordingly.

Heinrich Klaasen: I practice (hitting sixes off the back foot) it, it something I train a lot. I went back into the nets (during the break) and tried to figure it out and I have hit one or two today that brought a smile to my face. I challenged myself in the nets against spin and everything just clicked again, I'm very pleased. It's been a long couple of months, that break (of 9 days after the LSG game) definitely helped and we will be nice and fresh mentally, first into the playoffs and then into the World Cup. Supporting KKR tonight, we will definitely watch and support KKR tonight.

Stats round-up by Roshan Gede

Pat Cummins | SRH captain: It's pretty cool, it's awesome. We have won 6 out of 7 here, it has been great and amazing. I didn't know many guys coming into this season, but we have played great cricket and had some fun. Great bunch of guys. He (Abhishek) is amazing. I wouldn't want to bowl to him. It's scary as he plays with freedom, not only against pacers but also against spinners. Nitish is a class player, looks mature beyond his age, seems to sum up the game really well, he is perfect for our top-order. Really satisfying and exciting. I haven't played in finals before, we'll know in a few hours which game it is. Playing some really good cricket, excited for what's ahead.

Abhishek Sharma | Player of the Match: It's a matter of time for any batsman. My days are going good so I should utilize it for my team. I wanted to contribute as the target was big today. I think I have told this before, during SMAT I was clear how I was going to play and dominate (during IPL). He (Lara) was our coach as well, have done some work with him, he's in touch. That's helping me now. Just waiting for the loose balls, I am going hard against them and trying to put them (bowlers) under pressure. I was talking to Nitish, the more I was waiting it was getting easier for me. I was ready for that (playing against Harshal). I was trying to take a single but fortunately got a boundary (one of the balls.) I want to thank the crowd, special mention to pitch curator and groundsmen. They have given pitches that have suited our style.
